WEBVTT

00:04.134 --> 00:07.050
♪

00:10.097 --> 00:14.101
♪

00:19.019 --> 00:22.370
♪

00:25.503 --> 00:32.510
♪

01:37.488 --> 01:38.620
- Joey.

01:38.663 --> 01:40.404
- Hey, Steve.
What's up?

01:41.927 --> 01:44.104
Hey, Joe.
- Morning, Pops.

01:44.147 --> 01:47.194
This guy--

01:47.237 --> 01:49.326
You got another date coming up?

01:49.370 --> 01:51.023
Huh?
Go on.

01:51.067 --> 01:53.374
Just, you know,
you call her up,

01:53.417 --> 01:54.766
ask her to dinner,

01:54.810 --> 01:56.203
and you take her
someplace nice--

01:57.247 --> 01:58.205
- Huh, you're finally

01:58.248 --> 01:59.728
getting back out there.

01:59.771 --> 02:01.686
You know, putting the bachelor
life behind you...

02:01.730 --> 02:03.819
- Enough. Pops.

02:03.862 --> 02:05.125
- Listen,
she didn't show, okay?

02:05.168 --> 02:07.997
I had a burger and left.
That's it.

02:09.781 --> 02:12.915
- Eh, stop wallowing.

02:12.958 --> 02:15.483
Just, you get back
out there, you try again.

02:15.526 --> 02:17.615
I mean, it's like
this place, right?

02:17.659 --> 02:21.619
Put in your time,
show your worth.

02:21.663 --> 02:22.881
Look.

02:22.925 --> 02:24.709
You're a provider, Joey.

02:24.753 --> 02:25.710
All right?

02:25.754 --> 02:26.842
Any girl worth a damn

02:26.885 --> 02:29.410
would be crazy to pass that up.

02:29.453 --> 02:31.890
Don't wallow.

02:37.287 --> 02:41.161
♪

02:51.258 --> 02:53.956
- Let's see what you got,
tough guy!

03:10.799 --> 03:17.806
♪

03:26.118 --> 03:27.511
- Come on.
Let's go, let's go.

03:27.555 --> 03:29.774
What is that?

03:29.818 --> 03:31.689
- Trick or treat!

03:31.733 --> 03:33.213
- We're coming for you,
pretty boy.

03:33.256 --> 03:34.823
- Come on, keep running.
We're almost there.

03:34.866 --> 03:36.041
- Marco!

03:36.085 --> 03:37.304
- Come on, come on, work.

03:37.347 --> 03:38.609
- Polo!
- Come on.

03:38.653 --> 03:39.654
- Rick, open it!

03:39.697 --> 03:42.265
- I'm trying, I'm trying.

03:43.527 --> 03:45.660
- Go, go, go, go, go!

03:45.703 --> 03:48.837
- You can run but
you can't hide!

03:54.843 --> 03:56.323
Oh, God, Rick.

03:56.366 --> 03:58.977
- They can't get in.
Don't worry.

03:59.021 --> 04:02.024
Hey, hey.
It's okay.

04:02.067 --> 04:04.113
We're safe.

04:04.156 --> 04:07.247
It's over.

04:07.290 --> 04:09.553
- No, it isn't.

04:14.036 --> 04:15.733
- We've got
a real Vietnam War kit.

04:15.777 --> 04:18.519
- All right, tie him up
right over there.

04:21.826 --> 04:24.089
- Come on, let's go!

04:27.310 --> 04:28.485
Give me the key.
- Take it easy, buddy.

04:28.529 --> 04:30.182
- Thank you.
- Bring 'em down.

04:30.226 --> 04:32.359
- Oh, wow!

04:32.402 --> 04:34.926
This is...

04:34.970 --> 04:36.537
So I'm guessing
this wasn't, uh,

04:36.580 --> 04:40.105
the homecoming that
you kind of expected, huh?

04:40.149 --> 04:41.977
Fuck you.

04:46.024 --> 04:48.418
Oh, look at you.

04:48.462 --> 04:49.985
- Do whatever you want to me.

04:50.028 --> 04:51.334
But she doesn't deserve this.

04:51.378 --> 04:52.379
- No, no, no, no, no.

04:52.422 --> 04:55.425
She deserves a lot worse.

04:55.469 --> 04:57.775
- Don't hurt him, please!
- Shut up!

04:57.819 --> 04:59.211
I will do whatever
I goddamn want

04:59.255 --> 05:03.955
because it's my right to Purge.

05:20.015 --> 05:21.669
David, are you here?

05:24.715 --> 05:26.369
♪

05:26.413 --> 05:28.850
David?

05:28.893 --> 05:33.550
♪

05:44.126 --> 05:47.129
Is everything all right?

05:47.172 --> 05:49.087
What on Earth
are you doing outside?

05:49.131 --> 05:53.178
- I'm sorry, I know it's late.

05:53.222 --> 05:55.746
Well, no,
I tried to call.

05:55.790 --> 05:57.095
I kept calling and you never--

05:57.139 --> 05:58.793
- Yes, well,
after we closed our deal

05:58.836 --> 06:00.229
I did a bit of celebrating.

06:00.272 --> 06:02.492
I must not have heard
the phone, so.

06:02.536 --> 06:05.016
Come in.
Are you, uh,

06:05.060 --> 06:06.278
you're all right?

06:06.322 --> 06:08.846
- Sorry, I...

06:08.890 --> 06:12.110
Sorry.

06:12.154 --> 06:13.938
I didn't know what else to do.

06:13.982 --> 06:16.637
I'm...

06:16.680 --> 06:18.595
I'm confused,
I don't understand.

06:18.639 --> 06:19.857
- David, I made a decision
about tonight that I--

06:19.901 --> 06:21.119
- Actually, you know
what, Jane?

06:21.163 --> 06:24.688
Please allow me
to apologize for

06:24.732 --> 06:26.081
making you work tonight.

06:26.124 --> 06:28.083
Clearly a woman of your stature

06:28.126 --> 06:29.737
should have been at home
with her family, so

06:29.780 --> 06:32.348
I'm sorry.

06:32.392 --> 06:34.394
- Thank you.

06:34.437 --> 06:36.091
I appreciate that.

06:36.134 --> 06:37.875
- Anyway.

06:37.919 --> 06:39.094
What's on your mind?

06:42.184 --> 06:43.315
- Of course.

06:43.359 --> 06:45.361
State of the art
Sandin Security.

06:48.233 --> 06:49.583
Why?
Were you expecting some--

06:49.626 --> 06:51.498
- David, someone's coming
to kill you.

06:55.632 --> 06:59.462
- Lockdown initiated,
Mister Ryker.

06:59.506 --> 07:02.247
Sector one secure.

07:05.294 --> 07:07.862
♪

07:13.171 --> 07:16.000
- When did you know that
they were going to attack?

07:16.044 --> 07:18.089
- I--
- You looked right at me.

07:18.133 --> 07:20.570
And then you left
and went to her.

07:20.614 --> 07:22.485
- I wanted to make sure
you were both safe.

07:23.878 --> 07:29.623
You left
and you didn't come back.

07:29.666 --> 07:30.885
Jenna, where are you going?

07:30.928 --> 07:33.583
We're not done here.

07:38.762 --> 07:41.809
- Please pick up.
Please pick up.

07:41.852 --> 07:44.464
- Hi, it's Lila!
You know what to do.

07:47.902 --> 07:48.903
Can we not right now?

07:48.946 --> 07:50.252
- No. Answer me.

07:50.295 --> 07:53.168
- It doesn't matter.
- It does to me.

07:53.211 --> 07:54.517
- I--

07:54.561 --> 07:55.518
No.

07:55.562 --> 08:00.175
I don't.

08:00.218 --> 08:02.482
I don't know.
- I can't believe you.

08:02.525 --> 08:05.093
Do you know why I went
to that party tonight?

08:05.136 --> 08:08.226
Why I was sucking up
to all those assholes?

08:08.270 --> 08:09.793
Because we need that deal.

08:09.837 --> 08:11.447
Not just me.
You do, too.

08:12.579 --> 08:14.406
- Yes, you're goddamn right.

08:14.450 --> 08:16.321
Jenna, I know
how important it is

08:16.365 --> 08:18.976
to you to start giving
something back,

08:19.020 --> 08:21.501
to do some good for a change.

08:21.544 --> 08:24.025
And I want that too.

08:24.068 --> 08:27.724
I mean, we were 12 hours away
from changing everything,

08:27.768 --> 08:29.900
so I closed my eyes
and I started counting down.

08:29.944 --> 08:31.293
And where the hell were you?

08:31.336 --> 08:33.251
I was right there!
- Bullshit!

08:33.295 --> 08:35.471
You were upstairs trying to --
- Shut up, just shut up, Rick!

08:35.515 --> 08:38.126
Just, please, for one second,
and listen to me.

08:39.257 --> 08:41.912
I saw something tonight.

08:41.956 --> 08:44.306
Something I hoped wasn't true.

08:44.349 --> 08:45.525
And it's been building.

08:45.568 --> 08:47.875
I've watched it happen
for a while.

08:47.918 --> 08:51.182
And in the moment
you touched that gun,

08:51.226 --> 08:53.968
I saw your face,
and I knew.

08:54.011 --> 08:56.405
Tonight wasn't about me.

08:56.448 --> 08:58.102
And it wasn't about us.

08:58.146 --> 09:01.062
Tonight was all you.

09:01.105 --> 09:02.716
Look at what you were
willing to do.

09:02.759 --> 09:05.588
- I did what I had to do
to provide for this family.

09:05.632 --> 09:07.982
- Jesus Christ, Rick,
you almost shot a man!

09:08.025 --> 09:09.113
- Yes, and I would have
pulled the trigger

09:09.157 --> 09:12.073
if I had to, Jenna!

09:15.163 --> 09:16.643
♪

09:16.686 --> 09:21.386
I will do
anything for this family,

09:21.430 --> 09:23.432
so that she

09:23.475 --> 09:25.782
doesn't have to eat shit
the way I did.

09:25.826 --> 09:28.872
Hearing kids call her
"white trash."

09:28.916 --> 09:30.918
Buying groceries
with food stamps

09:30.961 --> 09:31.962
or clothes at Goodwill.

09:32.006 --> 09:33.834
That shit is in my bones.

09:33.877 --> 09:35.966
And I won't go back, all right?
I'll do whatever it takes.

09:36.010 --> 09:37.315
- Don't act like
I'm some spoiled brat.

09:37.359 --> 09:38.708
I didn't grow up like them.

09:38.752 --> 09:40.231
- No, but you didn't
grow up like me.

09:40.275 --> 09:41.232
- That's it.

09:41.276 --> 09:42.756
That's it, isn't it?

09:42.799 --> 09:44.105
You have something to prove,

09:44.148 --> 09:46.063
but not to me, to yourself.

09:46.107 --> 09:48.631
Getting that deal done,
it somehow means that you've--

09:48.675 --> 09:51.155
you've made it.

09:51.199 --> 09:53.767
Well, I just don't like
the person it makes you.

09:53.810 --> 09:55.333
Ever since we met Stanton,

09:55.377 --> 09:57.248
I've watched the man
I fell in love with

09:57.292 --> 09:59.076
turn into something
that scares me.

09:59.120 --> 10:01.165
Is that why
you left me there?

10:01.209 --> 10:02.689
To die?

10:02.732 --> 10:05.039
Because you were scared?

10:05.082 --> 10:07.476
It wasn't so you could just
run off with your girlfriend?

10:07.519 --> 10:09.304
- Rick! Rick, you are not
listening to me.

10:09.347 --> 10:12.089
It's not about Lila,
it's about you!

10:12.133 --> 10:14.352
I miss the person
who would have done anything

10:14.396 --> 10:17.138
to protect his family
from those people tonight,

10:17.181 --> 10:21.098
not become one of them.

10:21.142 --> 10:23.274
That's the man I love.

10:23.318 --> 10:26.103
That's the man I miss.

10:26.147 --> 10:28.758
- Jen...

10:37.637 --> 10:40.596
- Whoo!
You still with me?

10:40.640 --> 10:42.380
Don't die on me yet, buddy.

10:42.424 --> 10:44.600
Okay.

10:44.644 --> 10:45.645
Mm.

10:45.688 --> 10:47.342
- Step right up!

10:49.126 --> 10:51.694
- You wrote me.

10:51.738 --> 10:54.436
- Yeah.
To say goodbye.

10:54.479 --> 10:56.133
I can't keep fighting.

10:56.177 --> 10:57.526
Miguel, I can't.

10:57.569 --> 10:59.963
This night

11:00.007 --> 11:03.532
has taken everything.

11:03.575 --> 11:05.316
I just want to see Mom and Dad.

11:05.360 --> 11:06.883
- They're not ready
to see you yet.

11:06.927 --> 11:09.886
All right?
They want you here with me.

11:09.930 --> 11:10.974
- Miguel...

11:11.018 --> 11:14.151
- Pen.

11:20.201 --> 11:21.985
- Okay, all right!

11:22.029 --> 11:24.379
Enough.
Shall we?

11:24.422 --> 11:26.424
- You can have me,
but let my brother go.

11:26.468 --> 11:28.513
- Pen!
- I'm trying to save your life.

11:28.557 --> 11:31.821
- If you give in,
then I give up.

11:31.865 --> 11:34.998
And I'll be right behind you.

11:35.042 --> 11:37.784
- That's really sweet.

11:37.827 --> 11:40.874
But sorry, no deal.

11:40.917 --> 11:43.050
I'm gonna Purge both of you.

11:43.093 --> 11:44.399
- I should have killed you
when I had the chance.

11:44.442 --> 11:45.792
- Yeah, you probably
should have.

11:45.835 --> 11:48.011
But, you know,
hindsight being 20/20,

11:48.055 --> 11:49.404
that makes sense.

11:49.447 --> 11:54.452
- More like 10/10.

11:54.496 --> 11:57.107
- You know,

11:57.151 --> 11:59.283
for the longest time

11:59.327 --> 12:04.114
all I did was--was think
about killing you both.

12:04.158 --> 12:09.424
I went over it, like, a thousand
different times in my head.

12:09.467 --> 12:13.167
And I imagined
what the world would feel like

12:13.210 --> 12:14.821
without you in it.

12:14.864 --> 12:17.519
And eventually,

12:17.562 --> 12:21.349
it just got--
it just felt right.

12:23.481 --> 12:26.223
- Don't fucking touch her.

12:28.269 --> 12:30.793
- You know,
we're not that different,

12:30.837 --> 12:32.882
you and me.

12:32.926 --> 12:34.971
How's that?

12:35.015 --> 12:36.886
- Well, we, uh, we both kill

12:36.930 --> 12:40.455
because the government
says that it's okay.

12:40.498 --> 12:43.110
Hoorah, motherfucker, hoorah!

12:46.548 --> 12:49.420
All right, you ready?

12:57.559 --> 12:59.126
- Man.

12:59.169 --> 13:02.825
I gotta know.
Who are you?

13:02.869 --> 13:06.176
- All that matters right now
is that we get you inside.

13:09.049 --> 13:10.877
- Man, I know you.

13:10.920 --> 13:12.487
- I don't think so.
- Yeah.

13:12.530 --> 13:14.706
I do.

13:14.750 --> 13:16.230
You remember
those little candies?

13:16.273 --> 13:19.320
The fruity and mint?

13:20.887 --> 13:22.627
- You know the ones
I'm talking about?

13:23.890 --> 13:25.282
- Exactly.

13:25.326 --> 13:26.849
That's what you are, man.

13:32.115 --> 13:35.292
A goddamn lifesaver, man.
- I got you.

13:39.296 --> 13:46.303
♪

13:58.011 --> 14:00.752
- Hey, listen up!

14:00.796 --> 14:03.886
We get the Lost Horse
shipment finished today,

14:03.930 --> 14:05.714
first round's on me.

14:11.285 --> 14:14.897
♪

14:16.246 --> 14:18.988
Come on.
- I'll see you later.

14:19.032 --> 14:21.512
JJ, can I get one?

14:28.041 --> 14:31.566
Good day today.

14:31.609 --> 14:34.961
- Tell me you don't think
she's your friend.

14:36.484 --> 14:38.094
- No, you listen to me,
all right?

14:38.138 --> 14:42.055
She's management,
so, by definition, the enemy.

14:42.098 --> 14:43.273
- I'm gonna get you a cab.

14:43.317 --> 14:45.188
- She--she may smile at you,

14:45.232 --> 14:47.364
but she's the goddamn
Grim Reaper.

14:47.408 --> 14:48.800
- Hey, JJ, can you
get him a ride?

14:48.844 --> 14:51.020
- You got it.

14:51.064 --> 14:52.369
- Hey.

14:52.413 --> 14:53.893
- Did you call a doctor
about that?

14:53.936 --> 14:55.720
- I will next week.

14:55.764 --> 14:56.983
- I will tomorrow.

14:57.026 --> 14:58.114
Come on, you have to
have somebody

14:58.158 --> 14:59.115
take a look at that.

14:59.159 --> 15:01.465
- I'm fine, Joey.

15:01.509 --> 15:03.946
30 years on the line
breathing shit.

15:03.990 --> 15:05.730
What do you expect?

15:05.774 --> 15:08.951
- We have good union insurance.
That's what it's there for.

15:08.995 --> 15:10.997
- Yeah, well, I better
hurry up and use it

15:11.040 --> 15:12.520
before we go under.

15:12.563 --> 15:14.304
- We're not going anywhere.

15:14.348 --> 15:16.437
Saticoy has been there
for 50 years.

15:16.480 --> 15:18.395
Grandpa helped build the place.

15:18.439 --> 15:20.397
We make stuff that lasts.

15:20.441 --> 15:22.008
- Nothing lasts forever.

15:22.051 --> 15:24.358
I mean, sure, that wheel
will keep turning,

15:24.401 --> 15:26.360
till they find
a cheaper way to make it!

15:26.403 --> 15:28.362
- Okay, hey, rise and shine.

15:28.405 --> 15:29.929
Say good night to John,
everyone.

15:29.972 --> 15:31.756
- We're dinosaurs, Joey.

15:31.800 --> 15:35.717
And that meteor,
that meteor is coming.

15:36.848 --> 15:39.721
It's coming.

15:54.518 --> 15:55.955
- Look, I

15:55.998 --> 15:59.306
see what this night
has done to me.

15:59.349 --> 16:03.092
And I'm sorry.

16:03.136 --> 16:04.485
I'm so sorry.

16:04.528 --> 16:08.576
I got lost trying to
make sure that...

16:08.619 --> 16:10.621
that our baby's parents
don't have to struggle

16:10.665 --> 16:12.449
the way that mine did.

16:12.493 --> 16:13.885
And that's not an excuse.

16:13.929 --> 16:16.627
You're right.

16:16.671 --> 16:20.196
And I don't need any of it.

16:20.240 --> 16:25.071
I just need you.

16:25.114 --> 16:26.986
You're my home, Jen.

16:27.029 --> 16:32.339
Everything else
is just wallpaper.

16:32.382 --> 16:33.470
Here, let me--let me--

16:33.514 --> 16:34.906
- No, I got it.

16:45.091 --> 16:48.398
- You're gorgeous.

16:48.442 --> 16:51.097
- I'm going to bed.

16:53.751 --> 16:57.320
- I had a dream the other night
we were holding her.

16:57.364 --> 16:59.931
She opened her eyes
for the first time.

16:59.975 --> 17:04.066
And suddenly
she became a person.

17:04.110 --> 17:05.502
And she--she looked at me,

17:05.546 --> 17:07.330
and it was the most
incredible thing

17:07.374 --> 17:11.856
I've ever seen
in my entire life.

17:11.900 --> 17:14.424
And you--

17:14.468 --> 17:15.991
you gave me her,

17:16.035 --> 17:17.427
and I held her,

17:17.471 --> 17:21.388
and I...

17:21.431 --> 17:24.086
I started crying.

17:24.130 --> 17:28.003
She just fit so perfectly.

17:28.047 --> 17:30.005
It was like

17:30.049 --> 17:34.183
my arms were designed
to hold her.

17:37.012 --> 17:39.928
And that's all I want.

17:39.971 --> 17:42.974
That's all I need.

17:43.018 --> 17:46.761
- Come here.

17:46.804 --> 17:48.806
I love you so much.

17:48.850 --> 17:53.159
- I could stay right here
and be happy.

17:53.202 --> 17:55.248
But you want to keep going.

17:55.291 --> 17:57.250
Until when?

17:57.293 --> 17:59.556
When is it enough?

17:59.600 --> 18:00.644
- I don't know.

18:00.688 --> 18:02.472
- I know you want to provide.

18:02.516 --> 18:04.344
And I do too, but for me that
means

18:04.387 --> 18:09.000
knowing when you have
more than enough to be happy.

18:09.044 --> 18:11.873
What I saw tonight,
the excess, the privilege,

18:11.916 --> 18:14.963
nothing is worth
ending up like that.

18:15.006 --> 18:16.921
All that matters is

18:16.965 --> 18:20.577
who you are and
who you're with.

18:20.621 --> 18:23.885
- I don't want to lose you.

18:23.928 --> 18:27.106
Okay? I'll--
I'll do whatever it takes.

18:27.149 --> 18:30.848
- Then stop climbing,
or you will.

18:34.461 --> 18:35.418
♪

18:39.292 --> 18:41.337
- So first,

18:41.381 --> 18:43.948
I'm gonna take your eye.

18:43.992 --> 18:46.386
And then I'm gonna
take your sister.

18:46.429 --> 18:49.128
But before you bleed out,

18:49.171 --> 18:53.915
you're gonna see all of that.

18:53.958 --> 18:56.309
Well--

18:56.352 --> 18:57.745
or half of it, at least.

18:57.788 --> 19:01.227
Oh, ho, ho, ho.

19:01.270 --> 19:04.230
- So then get on with it.
- Okay!

19:06.014 --> 19:06.971
Oh.

19:07.015 --> 19:08.930
You know, when the, uh,

19:08.973 --> 19:11.541
when the cornea bursts,

19:11.585 --> 19:16.155
you'll see the most
spectacular colors.

19:16.198 --> 19:19.114
So enjoy that.

19:19.158 --> 19:23.292
Because after that,
