didn't even tell us to duck.

27:23.511 --> 27:25.469
Open the goddamn gate!
- Come on, yeah.

27:25.513 --> 27:27.254
- There she comes.

27:28.995 --> 27:30.213
We're getting the axe?

27:30.257 --> 27:31.388
No warning?

27:31.432 --> 27:32.651
What about severance?

27:34.043 --> 27:35.958
- Now, I know that
you're all angry.

27:36.002 --> 27:37.046
I am too.

27:37.090 --> 27:38.831
This isn't easy for anyone.

27:38.874 --> 27:40.615
- I saw the books.

27:40.659 --> 27:42.704
We were outperforming
last quarter.

27:42.748 --> 27:44.663
What the hell happened?
- We were.

27:44.706 --> 27:47.143
But not at
a steady enough rate.

27:47.187 --> 27:48.841
This just isn't sustainable.

27:48.884 --> 27:50.712
- So you pull the plug
and send us packing?

27:50.756 --> 27:52.018
- Forget it, Joe.

27:52.061 --> 27:53.889
They got an offer
they couldn't refuse.

27:53.933 --> 27:55.586
- Where are you sending
our jobs?

27:55.630 --> 27:57.066
- Half to Mexico,

27:57.110 --> 27:59.416
the other half to the
goddamn machines, right?

27:59.460 --> 28:00.461
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

28:02.028 --> 28:03.551
- Now, I know that some of you
have questions--

28:04.595 --> 28:05.988
Why don't you question this?

28:06.032 --> 28:07.860
- I'm sorry, I'm--
- Oh, yeah, "I'm sorry."

28:07.903 --> 28:09.731
Sorry doesn't pay our bills!

28:11.690 --> 28:14.083
- Or our health insurance.

28:14.127 --> 28:15.476
We have families.

28:15.519 --> 28:18.609
What are we supposed to do?

28:18.653 --> 28:20.002
- It's out of my hands.

28:20.046 --> 28:21.003
- Bullshit!

28:21.047 --> 28:22.091
- I'm sorry.

28:22.135 --> 28:24.398
- This is not right.

28:24.441 --> 28:25.529
- I'm sorry.

28:28.663 --> 28:30.621
- I told you.

28:30.665 --> 28:34.495
The Grim fucking Reaper.

28:44.592 --> 28:51.599
♪

29:04.003 --> 29:07.528
Come on.

29:07.571 --> 29:09.051
- I'm a clean man.
Lookit, look.

29:10.618 --> 29:12.402
- But what is
the $14,000 about?

29:12.446 --> 29:13.708
- He didn't help me
with anything.

29:15.188 --> 29:16.189
- This was 2015--

29:25.067 --> 29:28.549
I can't afford
the good shit no more.

29:31.378 --> 29:34.381
- String him up, boys!
Go fetch me that little lady.

29:34.424 --> 29:36.687
- You won't get away with this!

29:36.731 --> 29:38.951
- Demonstrations
erupted in Los Angeles today

29:38.994 --> 29:41.910
as new restrictions
were placed on water usage.

29:41.954 --> 29:43.999
- Congress will convene
a special session

29:44.043 --> 29:45.000
to resume debate.

29:46.872 --> 29:48.438
- As we can see here,
massive flooding

29:48.482 --> 29:50.266
along the coastline.

29:50.310 --> 29:52.094
- Oh, give me a break.
- We thank you for joining us.

29:52.138 --> 29:53.922
- Markets took
a major hit today

29:53.966 --> 29:56.272
as U.S. manufacturing
continues to decline.

29:56.316 --> 29:58.144
- Playing one is Zohan, Zoha--

29:58.187 --> 30:00.886
- And that ties it up
at the top of the hour--

30:00.929 --> 30:03.584
- Every day
you show up to your job

30:03.627 --> 30:05.978
on time, ready to work.

30:06.021 --> 30:07.980
You play by the rules,

30:08.023 --> 30:09.938
adhere to the social contract,

30:09.982 --> 30:12.245
because you know
it's the only way

30:12.288 --> 30:15.509
to conduct yourself
in a civilized society.

30:15.552 --> 30:18.860
And yet, all your hard work
and dedication

30:18.904 --> 30:20.819
is meaningless.

30:20.862 --> 30:22.821
Society screws you over.

30:22.864 --> 30:24.431
You get laid off.

30:24.474 --> 30:26.346
Your boss won't promote you.

30:26.389 --> 30:27.826
Your wife left.

30:27.869 --> 30:29.566
Your date stood you up.

30:29.610 --> 30:30.872
Over and over.

30:30.916 --> 30:33.788
You give, they take.

30:33.832 --> 30:35.616
So now what?

30:35.659 --> 30:37.052
It's simple.

30:37.096 --> 30:39.359
Don't wallow
in disappointment.

30:39.402 --> 30:42.884
Embrace the healing powers
of violence

30:42.928 --> 30:44.320
and Purge.

30:44.364 --> 30:47.149
This year.
Every year.

30:47.193 --> 30:50.239
Take charge of your future.

30:50.283 --> 30:52.720
I will be your guide.

30:54.853 --> 30:56.811
- All right, head up.
Act like you belong.

30:59.683 --> 31:02.512
- Two tickets! You don't know
what you're gonna win!

31:02.556 --> 31:05.080
- We should torch this place.

31:06.603 --> 31:10.694
- Shit.
Come, quick.

31:16.657 --> 31:18.006
- Let us out of here!

31:18.050 --> 31:20.269
- All right, when I tell you,
start running.

31:20.313 --> 31:21.531
- Miguel.
- And don't stop.

31:21.575 --> 31:26.797
- No.

31:26.841 --> 31:28.190
- Yeah, I do.
- Pen.

31:28.234 --> 31:29.452
- Just trust me.

31:29.496 --> 31:31.411
Come on.

31:31.454 --> 31:32.934
- Going once,
going twice,

31:32.978 --> 31:35.937
this woman is sold for $250.

31:35.981 --> 31:38.331
And now we have a gentleman
who is lean and of average...

31:38.374 --> 31:40.986
- You wanted to
blend in, right?

31:41.029 --> 31:42.552
So blend.

31:42.596 --> 31:44.380
- Let's start
the bidding at $50.

31:44.424 --> 31:45.947
Can I get $50?
Thank you very much.

31:45.991 --> 31:47.601
And $75, right down
to the front.

31:47.644 --> 31:48.776
How about $100?

31:48.819 --> 31:50.038
$100.
$100, in the back.

31:51.431 --> 31:52.693
Holy mass Penny?

31:52.736 --> 31:53.955
Goddess Penny, what happened?

31:53.999 --> 31:55.043
- Move. Let's go.

31:55.087 --> 31:56.392
- Penelope!

31:56.436 --> 31:57.393
Penelope!

31:57.437 --> 31:58.612
- Split up and find them

31:58.655 --> 32:00.005
before they can get to an exit.

32:00.048 --> 32:01.354
They couldn't have gotten far.

32:01.397 --> 32:02.833
Move, goddamn it!

32:02.877 --> 32:03.834
- Come on.

32:06.098 --> 32:09.231
- T-shirts!
T-shirts!

32:09.275 --> 32:13.801
